SIMPLE: drive-in
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: drive-in
<hw>drive-in</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any installation designed to
accommodate patrons while staying in their automobiles; especially an
outdoor movie theater in which patrons park in their vehicles to watch
the movie.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>drive-in</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: drive-in
<hw>drive-in</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>arranged to allow business to be
transacted while patrons remain in their vehicles; <as>as, a
<ex>drive-in</ex> window at a bank</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drive-through.</syn>
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>drive-in window</ent>⟦br⟧
